1.Test whether the process(exec() system call) that replaces old program data , will inherit
  the fd&#39;s or not.
2.Write a program such that parent process create two child processes,such that
  each child executes a separate task.
3. A program that replaces old program with new program data and is expected to display
    the currently running processes in a hierarchical tree format.
4.  A processs using execl() system call should replace a new command line program.
5.Write a program parent process wait untill ,while child process open a file and read file
  data into empty buffer.
6.Write a program, where functions of the program are called in the reverse order of
  their function calls from main().
7. Write a program child executes(exec()) a new program , while parent waits for
child task to get complete.
